UFO's are real. I have seen them twice....in 1967, and again in 1976. The first time, my much older brother, a career Air Force man then, woke me up from a sound sleep at 2:00 am, and told me to sit down on the floor next to the living room windows. He pointed toward an area in the clear starry sky, and told me to continue looking at it until I saw something move. I did, and something did move. It looked just like another star in the sky, (not within our atmosphere) but I had never seen a star move before, much less at the speeds it was moving. (I won't even venture to guess) It also made 90° and 180° turns without slowing down. It moved across great distances in seconds, in different directions, and could stop on a dime.My brother kept repeating, "We (Air Force) don't have anything that can move like that." It was all very interesting, but all I wanted to do was crawl back into bed, and go back to sleep! I had a 6 mo.old baby then, and I was exhausted.

The second UFO I saw (1976) was a lot closer. My husband and I were driving home from his brothers house where his 2 brothers and him were playing guitars or playing pool in his brothers basement. It was around 3:00 or 3:30 am, and there were no other cars on the road. As we were driving past a small county airport, a very bright yellow Orb pulled up along beside us, above the dirt shoulder of the road, outside of the passenger side window where I was sitting, about 6 feet (or less) away from me.(the window was up) It was very, very bright with no defined edges, and I couldn't see who or what was driving it. Then my husband saw it too, and he immediately began to pull the van onto the shoulder to stop. The moment he did that, the Orb vanished. It instantly disappeared!! I never felt any fear, I just felt like we were being observed. Unfortunately, my husband died over 12 years ago, so he can't corroborate this up close encounter. (Close Encounter Of The First Kind) I haven't seen any more UFO's in the past 46 years, but I can still hope, or perhaps initiate contact with ET's myself. (Close Encounters Of The Fifth Kind)
